
Target audience:
This repo is intended for developer use.  It contains source code that needs to
go through a "build" process to construct a bundle (.zip) that can be uploaded
to Lambda either directly, or via an S3 bucket.


Software:
- Docker for OS X   (follow installation instructions on Docker's docs.)
- Homebrew package manager  (follow Homebrew's installation docs.)
- AWS SAM CLI
   - installed from Homebrew.
   - install docs:   https://docs.aws.amazon.com/serverless-application-model/latest/developerguide/serverless-sam-cli-install-mac.html
- Python 3.7.7
   - Lambda uses a Python 3.7.7 run-time environment
   - SAM CLI must build your Lambda's dependencies using Python 3.7.7
   - AWS SAM CLI utility uses Python 3.7.7
   * Gets installed automatically for you by Homebrew when you use Homebrew
     to install the AWS SAM CLI utility.


Making the zip:
* These instructions assume you're using OS X.
- clone this repo.
- install Docker, if not yet installed on your dev computer.
- install Homebrew, if not yet installed on your dev computer.
- Follow these instructions to install AWS SAM CLI utility:
    https://docs.aws.amazon.com/serverless-application-model/latest/developerguide/serverless-sam-cli-install-mac.html
